text:
Light laughs the breeze in her castle of sunshine;
Babbles the bee in a stolid ear;
Pipe the sweet birds in ignorant cadence, --
Ah, what sagacity perished here!

Lightly the breeze laughs in her sunlit castle;  
The bee goes murmuring in a dull ear;  
Sweet birds are piping in unwitting rhythm, --  
Ah, what wisdom vanished here!

